To make this work seamlessly on your Hostinger website, we need to solve a tricky technical problem: **The Click-Through Issue**.

If we just put a full-screen transparent layer over your website, users won't be able to click any buttons on your actual website.

**The Solution:**
1.  I will update the App to communicate with your website.
2.  The Widget will stay **small** (just the button) so your website works normally.
3.  When you click "Speak to Neha", the widget tells your website to **expand** to full screen for the call.

Here are the updated files to enable this logic:

# Updated files:

## components/CallFloatingButton.tsx

Adjusted positioning to fit perfectly inside the compact widget iframe.

## App.tsx

Added logic to send 'resize' messages to the parent website when the call starts/ends.

---

### **Step 1: Deploy Your App**
You cannot embed the code directly from your local computer. You must deploy this React app to the cloud first.

1.  Push your code to **GitHub**.
2.  Go to **[Vercel.com](https://vercel.com)** (it's free).
3.  Import your GitHub repo and click **Deploy**.
4.  Once done, Vercel will give you a URL (e.g., `https://next2dubai-neha.vercel.app`). **Copy this URL.**

---

### **Step 2: The Copy-Paste Embed Code**
Go to your **Hostinger Website Builder (Horizon)**.
1.  Find the option to **"Add Custom Code"** or **"Embed Code"**.
2.  Paste the following code into the **Body - End** section (or Footer).
3.  **IMPORTANT:** Replace `YOUR_VERCEL_APP_URL` with the link you got from Vercel.

```html
<!-- Neha AI Widget Embed Code -->
<div id="neha-widget-container">
  <iframe 
    id="neha-widget-frame"
    src="YOUR_VERCEL_APP_URL"
    allow="microphone; autoplay"
    style="width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none; overflow: hidden;"
  ></iframe>
</div>

<style>
  #neha-widget-container {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 10px;
    right: 10px;
    width: 220px;  /* Initially small - just enough for the button */
    height: 100px; /* Initially small */
    z-index: 999999;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    background: transparent;
  }

  /* Mobile Adjustments */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    #neha-widget-container {
      bottom: 5px;
      right: 5px;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Listen for messages from Neha to expand/collapse the widget
  window.addEventListener('message', function(event) {
    var widget = document.getElementById('neha-widget-container');

    if (event.data.type === 'resize-widget') {
      if (event.data.expanded) {
        // Expand to full screen when calling
        widget.style.width = '100vw';
        widget.style.height = '100vh';
        widget.style.bottom = '0';
        widget.style.right = '0';
        widget.style.borderRadius = '0';
      } else {
        // Shrink back to button size when call ends
        widget.style.width = '220px';
        widget.style.height = '100px';
        widget.style.bottom = '10px';
        widget.style.right = '10px';
      }
    }
  });
</script>
<!-- End Neha Widget -->

To fix the "Connection Failed" error on your website, we need to identify the exact cause. It is usually one of three things:
1.  **Microphone Permission:** The website (Hostinger) iframe is blocking the microphone.
2.  **API Key Missing:** The `API_KEY` is not being read correctly in your deployed environment.
3.  **Network/Model Issue:** The AI model is temporarily unavailable.

I have updated `App.tsx` to give you a **specific error message** instead of a generic "Connection Failed". This will tell you exactly what is wrong. I also added a check to ensure your API Key is actually loaded.

I have also updated the floating button to ensure it sits correctly in the corner.

# Updated files:

## App.tsx

Added detailed error handling. It now checks if the API Key is present and catches Microphone errors separately. The alert will now tell you exactly why it failed (e.g., "API Key missing", "Microphone access denied", or a specific network error).

## components/CallFloatingButton.tsx

Adjusted the z-index and touch handling to ensure it remains clickable inside the iframe on all devices.

### **How to Fix the Embed Code on Hostinger**

If the error says **"Microphone access denied"**, you must update your embed code on Hostinger. Ensure you have `allow="microphone"` in the iframe tag.

**Use this exact code in Hostinger (Custom Code section):**

```html
<!-- Neha AI Widget Embed Code -->
<div id="neha-widget-container">
  <iframe 
    id="neha-widget-frame"
    src="YOUR_VERCEL_APP_URL" 
    allow="microphone; autoplay; camera"
    allowusermedia
    style="width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none; overflow: hidden;"
  ></iframe>
</div>

<style>
  #neha-widget-container {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 10px;
    right: 10px;
    width: 220px;  /* Compact size for button */
    height: 100px; 
    z-index: 999999;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    background: transparent;
    border-radius: 50px; /* Matches button curve */
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Logic to expand/collapse widget
  window.addEventListener('message', function(event) {
    var widget = document.getElementById('neha-widget-container');

    if (event.data.type === 'resize-widget') {
      if (event.data.expanded) {
        // Full screen for call
        widget.style.width = '100vw';
        widget.style.height = '100vh';
        widget.style.bottom = '0';
        widget.style.right = '0';
        widget.style.borderRadius = '0';
      } else {
        // Compact for button
        widget.style.width = '220px';
        widget.style.height = '100px';
        widget.style.bottom = '10px';
        widget.style.right = '10px';
      }
    }
  });
</script>
```

**Important:** Replace `YOUR_VERCEL_APP_URL` with your actual deployed link.

To fix the issue where the app "opens a small tab" (which is actually the **Alert Pop-up** saying "Connection Failed") and to ensure direct, smooth access, I have removed all browser pop-ups. Errors will now appear nicely inside the widget.

I have also updated the code to handle the "Connection Failed" scenario gracefully with a **Retry** button.

### **1. Changes Made**
*   **Removed Pop-ups**: The app will no longer use `alert()` boxes that look like "small tabs".
*   **Smart Error Handling**: If the connection fails (e.g., Network or Mic issue), a red notification will appear smoothly inside the app.
*   **Retry Logic**: Added a button to retry the connection immediately if it fails.

### **2. Updated Embed Code (Crucial Step)**
You must update the code on your **Hostinger** website to ensure the "Direct Access" works and the widget expands correctly.

**Go to Hostinger -> Custom Code (Footer) -> Replace with this:**

```html
<!-- Neha AI Widget Embed Code -->
<div id="neha-widget-container">
  <iframe 
    id="neha-widget-frame"
    src="YOUR_VERCEL_APP_URL" 
    allow="microphone; autoplay; camera"
    style="width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none; overflow: hidden; background: transparent;"
  ></iframe>
</div>

<style>
  #neha-widget-container {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 10px;
    right: 10px;
    width: 240px;  /* Button Size */
    height: 100px; 
    z-index: 999999;
    transition: all 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.8, 0.25, 1);
    background: transparent;
    border-radius: 50px;
  }

  /* When call is active (class added by script) */
  #neha-widget-container.active {
    width: 100vw !important;
    height: 100vh !important;
    bottom: 0 !important;
    right: 0 !important;
    border-radius: 0 !important;
  }
</style>

<script>
  window.addEventListener('message', function(event) {
    var widget = document.getElementById('neha-widget-container');
    if (event.data.type === 'resize-widget') {
      if (event.data.expanded) {
        widget.classList.add('active');
      } else {
        widget.classList.remove('active');
      }
    }
  });
</script>
```

### **3. Updated Application Files**

# Updated files:

## App.tsx

Removed `alert()`. Implemented `errorMessage` state. Passed error handler to Notification component. Added Retry logic.

## components/LeadNotification.tsx

Updated to handle Error types (Red styling) and Success types (Green styling).

## components/CallOverlay.tsx

Added UI for "Connecting..." state and Error state with Retry button.

To ensure the "Speak to Neha" button appears directly on your homepage without any extra clicks, popups, or black screens, we need to adjust the **Button Positioning** and the **Embed Code**.

### **1. The Problem**
Hostinger's "Widget" element wraps code in its own container (the "small popup" you see).
**The Fix:** You must not use the "Widget" element. You must use the **"Custom Code"** element and place it in the **Footer** or **Body End**.

### **2. Code Updates**
I am updating the button to sit perfectly inside a small, transparent iframe so it looks like a native part of your site.

# Updated files:

## components/CallFloatingButton.tsx

Changed positioning from `fixed` to `absolute` and adjusted margins so it fits perfectly inside the embed iframe without being cut off.

## App.tsx

Added a `ready` signal to ensure the iframe loads transparently before showing the button.

---

### **3. The Correct Embed Code (Crucial Step)**

**Do not** use a "Widget" or "Button" element in Hostinger.
**Do** use a "Custom Code" block.

1.  Go to **Website Settings** -> **Integrations** -> **Custom Code**.
2.  Paste this into the **Body** section.
3.  **Replace** `YOUR_VERCEL_APP_URL` with your actual link.

```html
<!-- Neha AI Direct Embed -->
<div id="neha-container" style="position: fixed; bottom: 20px; right: 20px; width: 250px; height: 100px; z-index: 9999999; border: none; background: transparent;">
  <iframe 
    id="neha-frame"
    src="YOUR_VERCEL_APP_URL"
    allow="microphone; autoplay; camera"
    style="width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none; background: transparent; overflow: hidden;"
    scrolling="no"
  ></iframe>
</div>

<script>
  // This script listens for the call to start/end and resizes the iframe
  window.addEventListener('message', function(event) {
    var container = document.getElementById('neha-container');
    var frame = document.getElementById('neha-frame');

    if (event.data.type === 'resize-widget') {
      if (event.data.expanded) {
        // EXPAND: Full screen for the call
        container.style.width = '100%';
        container.style.height = '100%';
        container.style.bottom = '0';
        container.style.right = '0';
        container.style.borderRadius = '0';
      } else {
        // SHRINK: Back to just the button
        container.style.width = '250px';
        container.style.height = '100px';
        container.style.bottom = '20px';
        container.style.right = '20px';
      }
    }
  });
</script>
```

**Why this works:**
*   It creates a transparent box in the corner.
*   Inside is your "Speak to Neha" button.
*   When you click it, the script expands the box to cover the screen for the call.
*   When you hang up, it shrinks back to the corner.

### **2. CRITICAL: Update your Hostinger Embed Code**

You MUST update your Hostinger Embed code because the size logic has changed. The widget now tells the browser exactly how big it needs to be (Card vs Full).

**Copy and Paste this into Hostinger -> Custom Code (Body End):**

```html
<!-- Neha AI Card Embed -->
<div id="neha-container" style="position: fixed; bottom: 20px; right: 20px; width: 350px; height: 500px; z-index: 999999; border: none; background: transparent;">
  <iframe 
    id="neha-frame"
    src="YOUR_VERCEL_APP_URL"
    allow="microphone; autoplay; camera"
    style="width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none; background: transparent; overflow: hidden;"
    scrolling="no"
  ></iframe>
</div>

<style>
  /* Mobile Responsive: Center on mobile */
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    #neha-container {
      right: 50% !important;
      transform: translateX(50%) !important;
      bottom: 10px !important;
      width: 90% !important;
      max-width: 350px !important;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  window.addEventListener('message', function(event) {
    var container = document.getElementById('neha-container');

    if (event.data.type === 'resize-widget') {
      if (event.data.view === 'full') {
        // FULL SCREEN (Call/Chat Mode)
        container.style.width = '100%';
        container.style.height = '100%';
        container.style.bottom = '0';
        container.style.right = '0';
        container.style.borderRadius = '0';
        // Reset mobile transform
        container.style.transform = 'none';
        container.style.right = '0 !important';
      } else {
        // CARD SIZE (Idle Mode)
        container.style.width = '350px';
        container.style.height = '500px';
        container.style.bottom = '20px';
        container.style.right = '20px';
        container.style.borderRadius = '0';

        // Re-apply mobile centering if on mobile
        if (window.innerWidth <= 480) {
             container.style.right = '50%';
             container.style.transform = 'translateX(50%)';
        }
      }
    }
  });
</script>

